[1] Case updates
- Tue 18 Dec 2018. Epidemiological situation report, Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=89a4ad0ad2

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 17 Dec 2018:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 542, 494 confirmed and 48 probable. In total, there have been 319 deaths (271 among confirmed and 48 among probable cases) and 192 people have recovered.
- 96 suspected cases under investigation.
- 3 new confirmed cases, including 1 in Katwa, 1 in Komanda, and 1 in Mabalako.
- 4 new confirmed case deaths, 2 in Beni, 1 in Butembo, and 1 in Mabalako (1 community death)
- 6 new recoveries, including 4 discharged from the Beni Ebola treatment center (ETC) and 2 from the Butembo ETC.

News of the response
Vaccination
-----------
- Continued wide-belt vaccination (or ring plus) in Otomaber (in Komanda health zone, Ituri) and Aloya (in Mabalako health zone, North Kivu).
- Continued immunization of primary care providers in the Goma health zone [North Kivu].
- Since vaccination began on 8 Aug 2018, 48 781 people have been vaccinated, including 19 060 in Beni, 8858 in Katwa, 5335 in Mabalako, 5144 in Butembo, 2208 in Kalunguta, 1663 in Mandima, [for the remaining vaccination figures, see the source URL above].
- The only vaccine to be used in this outbreak is the rVSV-ZEBOV vaccine, manufactured by the Merck pharmaceutical group, following approval by the Ethics Committee in its decision of 19 May 2018.

Video: The response against Ebola in images -- Ebola awareness by students

